'''Kamalakanta Jena''' ({{Lang-or|<U+0B15><U+0B2E><U+0B33><U+0B3E><U+0B15><U+0B3E><U+0B28><U+0B4D><U+0B24> <U+0B1C><U+0B47><U+0B28><U+0B3E>}}) is an [[Oriya language|Oriya]] [[writer]] from [[Orissa]], [[India]].

==Early life and education==
Kamalakanta Jena was born on 25 April 1971 in the village Januganj of [[Balasore district]] in [[Orissa]], [[India]]. He completed his matriculation from Remuna High School, [[Remuna]], [[Balasore]] and graduation from [[Fakir Mohan College]], Balasore. Jena has worked on Hot Plasma as Research Scholar in Regional Research laboratory, Bhubaneswar.

==Profession==
He joined Orissa Education Service (OES) under Department of Higher Education, Orissa in 1999 at Government College, [[Sundargarh]], Orissa. Now, he is working in Governemt Women's Junior College, Sundargarh.

==Writing career==
Kamalakanta Jena started writing at the age of 17 years. His first article was published in Chalachitra Jagat, cine monthly published from [[Cuttack]], Orissa. Subsequently, his articles were published in Sambad, daily newspaper from Orissa. He has written more than 600 articles in various magazines published inside and outside Orissa. He is best known for lucid writings on [[popular science]]. He has written text books for school and college students. He has written more than 10 books on Popular Science.
* Barsa Bijulira Khela<ref>[http://www.vidyapuri.com/store/items/author/350 vidyapuri.com: KAMALAKANTA JENA]</ref>
* Paribesa Sikhya
* Solar cells grow thinner, but glow brighter <ref>[http://www.indiaenvironmentportal.org.in/category/author/kamalakanta-jena indiaenvironmentportal.org.in: Solar cells grow thinner, but glow brighter]</ref>
==Awards==
He has been felicitated by various organisations including Bigyan Prachar Samiti, Orissa and awarded 'Prakruti Bandhu Puraskar' by Government of Orissa.
* Felicitated by Ispat Sahitya Sansad. <ref>[http://www.orissabarta.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=6166:ispat-sahitya-sansad-celebrates-40th-anniversary&catid=35:top-stories orissabarta.com: Ispat Sahitya Sansad celebrates 40th Anniversary]</ref>

